dcterms:description: COSET is a recently proposed benchmark framework that aims at providing a consistent baseline for evaluating the performance of neural program embeddings. It contains a dataset consisting of close to 85K programs developed by a large number of programmers while solving ten coding problems. Programs are handpicked to ensure sufficient variations and were manually analyzed and labeled.
dcterms:title: COSET
